=== Testbench

Two testbenches, one per `LANES` variant, share the same
stimulus shape: open CS, clock 256 SCLK rises, sample the
slave's output on each rise (mode-0 sampling) and assert the
reconstructed byte stream is `0, 1, 2, ... 255`. The 4-lane TB
reassembles bytes as `{second_sample, first_sample}` to match
the host-side QUADSPI assembly.

<<tb_spi_1lane.sv>>=
`timescale 1ns/1ps

module tb_spi_1lane;
   reg       cs_n = 1'b1;
   reg       sclk = 1'b0;
   wire [3:0] io;

   spi #(.LANES(1)) dut (.cs_n(cs_n), .sclk(sclk), .io(io));

   integer  i, b;
   reg [7:0] rx;
   integer  errs;

   initial begin
      errs = 0;
      #20 cs_n = 1'b0;
      #5;
      for (b = 0; b < 256; b = b + 1) begin
         rx = 8'd0;
         for (i = 0; i < 8; i = i + 1) begin
            #5 sclk = 1'b1;
            rx = {rx[6:0], io[1]};
            #5 sclk = 1'b0;
         end
         if (rx !== b[7:0]) begin
            $display("FAIL byte %0d: got %02x expected %02x", b, rx, b[7:0]);
            errs = errs + 1;
         end
      end
      #5 cs_n = 1'b1;
      #20;
      if (errs == 0) $display("PASS tb_spi_1lane: 256 bytes match");
      else           $display("FAIL tb_spi_1lane: %0d byte mismatches", errs);
      $finish;
   end
endmodule
@

<<tb_spi_quad.sv>>=
`timescale 1ns/1ps

module tb_spi_quad;
   reg       cs_n = 1'b1;
   reg       sclk = 1'b0;
   wire [3:0] io;

   spi #(.LANES(4)) dut (.cs_n(cs_n), .sclk(sclk), .io(io));

   integer    b;
   reg [3:0]  lo, hi;
   reg [7:0]  rx;
   integer    errs;

   initial begin
      errs = 0;
      #20 cs_n = 1'b0;
      #5;
      for (b = 0; b < 256; b = b + 1) begin
         #5 sclk = 1'b1;
         lo = io;
         #5 sclk = 1'b0;
         #5 sclk = 1'b1;
         hi = io;
         #5 sclk = 1'b0;
         rx = {hi, lo};
         if (rx !== b[7:0]) begin
            $display("FAIL byte %0d: got %02x expected %02x", b, rx, b[7:0]);
            errs = errs + 1;
         end
      end
      #5 cs_n = 1'b1;
      #20;
      if (errs == 0) $display("PASS tb_spi_quad: 256 bytes match");
      else           $display("FAIL tb_spi_quad: %0d byte mismatches", errs);
      $finish;
   end
endmodule
@

=== Build fragment

Two synthesis runs over the single `verilog/spi.v` source, each
overriding the `LANES` macro on the yosys command line. The
shared `verilog/spi.pcf` feeds nextpnr-ice40 for both. The two
sims and two bitstreams hang off the top-level `sim` and
`bitstream` aggregates so a bare `make` builds everything.

<<spi.mk>>=
SPI_VS := verilog/spi.v

build/spi/spi_1lane.json: $(SPI_VS) | build/spi
	cd build/spi && yosys -q -p "read_verilog ../../verilog/spi.v; chparam -set LANES 1 spi; synth_ice40 -top spi -json spi_1lane.json"

build/spi/spi_quad.json: $(SPI_VS) | build/spi
	cd build/spi && yosys -q -p "read_verilog ../../verilog/spi.v; chparam -set LANES 4 spi; synth_ice40 -top spi -json spi_quad.json"

build/spi/spi_1lane.asc: build/spi/spi_1lane.json verilog/spi.pcf
	cd build/spi && nextpnr-ice40 --$(DEVICE) --package $(PACKAGE) --json spi_1lane.json --pcf ../../verilog/spi.pcf --asc spi_1lane.asc --freq 100 -q

build/spi/spi_quad.asc: build/spi/spi_quad.json verilog/spi.pcf
	cd build/spi && nextpnr-ice40 --$(DEVICE) --package $(PACKAGE) --json spi_quad.json --pcf ../../verilog/spi.pcf --asc spi_quad.asc --freq 100 -q

build/spi/spi_1lane.bin: build/spi/spi_1lane.asc
	cd build/spi && icepack spi_1lane.asc spi_1lane.bin

build/spi/spi_quad.bin: build/spi/spi_quad.asc
	cd build/spi && icepack spi_quad.asc spi_quad.bin

tb/tb_spi_1lane.sv: src/spi.nw | tb
	cd tb && tangle tb_spi_1lane.sv < ../$<

tb/tb_spi_quad.sv: src/spi.nw | tb
	cd tb && tangle tb_spi_quad.sv < ../$<

build/spi/sim_1lane: tb/tb_spi_1lane.sv $(SPI_VS) | build/spi
	cd build/spi && verilator --Mdir obj_1lane -Wall --binary --top-module tb_spi_1lane ../../tb/tb_spi_1lane.sv ../../verilog/spi.v
	cd build/spi && obj_1lane/Vtb_spi_1lane
	@touch $@

build/spi/sim_quad: tb/tb_spi_quad.sv $(SPI_VS) | build/spi
	cd build/spi && verilator --Mdir obj_quad -Wall --binary --top-module tb_spi_quad ../../tb/tb_spi_quad.sv ../../verilog/spi.v
	cd build/spi && obj_quad/Vtb_spi_quad
	@touch $@

bitstream: build/spi/spi_1lane.bin build/spi/spi_quad.bin
sim: build/spi/sim_1lane build/spi/sim_quad
@

=== Hardware test plan

Two phases, each one fenced block per `(mode, prescaler)` so a
failure pins down exactly which (lane-count, SCLK) pair broke.
Every block reflashes the MP135 firmware from `flash.tsv`,
loads the matching bitstream, opens the MP135 console, sets the
prescaler, and issues the raw bench command. The success
sentinel is `firsterr` --- it appears in the bench summary line
only after the whole megabyte has been validated against the
incrementing pattern.

The prescaler sweep covers 203 (~3.25 MHz wire), 63 (~10 MHz),
15 (~41.5 MHz), 5 (~83 MHz), 2 (~166 MHz), and 1 (~332 MHz);
timeouts shrink with prescaler since the bench finishes faster
at higher SCLK.

<<TEST.md>>=
Phase 1 -- 1-lane sweep at presc=203.

